<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title><%= pageTitle %> | MyTaxCalcs</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Use the free capital gains tax calculator to estimate short-term and long-term capital gains tax, net investment income tax, and total estimated tax.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">

  <meta name="google-site-verification" content="TT2j7SglafccBK-Nfk4l1XVIDXEJdSmyQJf2wL9QY0o" />

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

  <script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549"
     crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="small-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">
        <span class="logo-icon">💵</span>
        <span>MyTaxCalcs</span>
      </a>

      <div class="nav-links">
  <a href="/">Home</a>
  <a href="/calculators">Calculators</a>
  <a href="/california-income-tax-calculator">States</a>
  <a href="/about">About</a>
  <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
</div>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="container two-column">
    <section class="card">
      <h1>Capital Gains Tax Calculator</h1>
      <p>Estimate federal tax on the profit from selling stocks, crypto, real estate, or other assets.</p>

      <form method="POST" action="/capital-gains-tax-calculator" class="form">
        <label>
          Filing status
          <select name="filingStatus">
            <option value="single" <%= form.filingStatus === "single" ? "selected" : "" %>>Single</option>
            <option value="marriedJoint" <%= form.filingStatus === "marriedJoint" ? "selected" : "" %>>Married Filing Jointly</option>
            <option value="marriedSeparate" <%= form.filingStatus === "marriedSeparate" ? "selected" : "" %>>Married Filing Separately</option>
            <option value="headHousehold" <%= form.filingStatus === "headHousehold" ? "selected" : "" %>>Head of Household</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Holding period
          <select name="holdingPeriod">
            <option value="long" <%= form.holdingPeriod === "long" ? "selected" : "" %>>Long-term, more than 1 year</option>
            <option value="short" <%= form.holdingPeriod === "short" ? "selected" : "" %>>Short-term, 1 year or less</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Sale price
          <input type="number" name="salePrice" value="<%= form.salePrice || '' %>" placeholder="150000" min="0" required>
        </label>

        <label>
          Purchase price / cost basis
          <input type="number" name="purchasePrice" value="<%= form.purchasePrice || '' %>" placeholder="80000" min="0" required>
        </label>

        <label>
          Selling costs
          <input type="number" name="sellingCosts" value="<%= form.sellingCosts || '' %>" placeholder="5000" min="0">
        </label>

        <label>
          Capital improvements
          <input type="number" name="improvements" value="<%= form.improvements || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0">
        </label>

        <label>
          Capital losses to offset gains
          <input type="number" name="capitalLosses" value="<%= form.capitalLosses || '' %>" placeholder="0" min="0">
        </label>

        <label>
          Other taxable income
          <input type="number" name="otherTaxableIncome" value="<%= form.otherTaxableIncome || '' %>" placeholder="85000" min="0">
        </label>

        <button type="submit">Calculate Capital Gains Tax</button>
      </form>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Estimated Results</h2>

      <% if (!result) { %>
        <p class="muted">Enter sale, basis, income, and holding period information to estimate capital gains tax.</p>
      <% } else { %>
        <div class="results">
          <p><span>Tax year:</span> <strong><%= result.taxYear %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Sale price:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.salePrice).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Adjusted basis:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.adjustedBasis).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Gross capital gain:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.grossGain).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Capital losses:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.capitalLosses).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Net taxable gain:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.netGain).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Estimated capital gains tax:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.estimatedCapitalGainsTax).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Estimated NIIT:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.estimatedNIIT).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Total estimated tax:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.totalEstimatedTax).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Effective tax rate on gain:</span> <strong><%= (result.effectiveCapitalGainsRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</strong></p>
        </div>

        <p class="state-message"><%= result.taxMethod %></p>
      <% } %>

      <p class="disclaimer">Estimate only. Not tax, legal, accounting, investment, or financial advice.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section class="container content seo-content">
    <p class="eyebrow dark">Capital Gains Tax Guide</p>
    <h2>How this capital gains tax calculator works</h2>
    <p>
      This calculator estimates the federal tax that may apply when you sell an asset for more
      than your adjusted basis. It can be used for planning around stocks, crypto, real estate,
      business property, or other assets, but it does not replace official tax software or a tax professional.
    </p>

    <div class="seo-grid">
      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Cost basis</h3>
        <p>
          Cost basis generally starts with what you paid for the asset. This calculator also lets
          you add selling costs and capital improvements to estimate adjusted basis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Short-term gains</h3>
        <p>
          Short-term gains are generally gains on assets held for one year or less and are estimated
          using ordinary federal income tax brackets.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-mini-card">
        <h3>Long-term gains</h3>
        <p>
          Long-term gains are generally gains on assets held for more than one year and may qualify
          for lower federal capital gains tax rates.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Capital gains tax FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is capital gains tax?</h3>
        <p>
          Capital gains tax is tax on profit from selling an asset for more than its adjusted basis.
          The tax treatment can depend on the asset type, holding period, filing status, income, and losses.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is the difference between short-term and long-term capital gains?</h3>
        <p>
          Short-term gains generally apply to assets held for one year or less. Long-term gains generally
          apply to assets held for more than one year and may qualify for lower federal tax rates.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Does this calculator include state capital gains tax?</h3>
        <p>
          No. This calculator focuses on federal estimates. Some states tax capital gains as ordinary income,
          while others may have different rules or no state income tax.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is Net Investment Income Tax?</h3>
        <p>
          Net Investment Income Tax is an additional federal tax that may apply to certain investment income
          when income is above specific thresholds. This calculator includes a simplified NIIT estimate.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I use this calculator for tax filing?</h3>
        <p>
          No. This calculator is for educational planning only. For filing, use official tax forms,
          tax software, or a qualified tax professional.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>
  </section>

 <section class="container content related-calculators">
  <p class="eyebrow dark">Related Calculators</p>
  <h2>More tax calculators</h2>

  <div class="related-grid">
